OUTA is heading to the courts to challenge another attempt by Dudu Myeni to escape her lifetime delinquency order. Outa's Chief Legal Officer, advocate Stefanie Fick, speaks more on this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former SAA board chairperson Dudu Myeni is expected to return to the High Court in Pretoria on Monday morning. She wants the enforcement of the lifetime delinquency order against her removed, pending the outcome of the appeal. WATCH: Myeni continues to fight delinquency case Myeni was declared a delinquent director for life in May last year but she filed an urgent appeal last month. The Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse brought the initial application to have her declared a delinquent director. It accused her of plunging SAA into financial chaos while she was board chairperson. 